This test aims to test USB port connectivity by verifying the correct functioning of all different type of USB devices e.g. pen drives, mice, music players, keyboards, cameras, headphones etc.
<dl>
  <dt>Plug a USB device in and attempt to use it</dt>
      <dd>The device should be correctly recognised</dd>
      <dd>The software normally used with the device should function normally</dd>
      <dd>The device should behave as expected</dd>
      <dd>The USB device should work in every port</dd>
      <dd>You should be able to disconnect and re-connect the USB device correctly without errors</dd>
  <dt>If the device is a USB3.0 storage device and you have a USB3.0 port, transfer a large file between the two</dt>
      <dd>The transfer should be above USB2.0 speed</dd>
<dl>

<strong>If you answer 'yes' to all questions, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'passed' result.
If you answer 'no' to any question, then please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> 'failed' and <a href="../../buginstructions">file a bug</a>. Please be sure to include the bug number when you <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> your result.</strong>
